#~ msgid "KrausChannel"
#~ msgstr "KrausChannel"

#~ msgid ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.KrausChannel` is a"
#~ " base class for digital noise models"
#~ " that use Kraus operators to "
#~ "represent quantum noise channels. Kraus "
#~ "operators can be used to represent "
#~ "a generic quantum channel :math:`\\mathcal{E}`"
#~ " acting on a density matrix "
#~ ":math:`\\rho` as:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.KrausChannel` es "
#~ "una clase base para modelos de "
#~ "ruido digital que usan operadores de "
#~ "Kraus para representar canales de ruido"
#~ " cuántico. Los operadores de Kraus se"
#~ " pueden usar para representar un "
#~ "canal cuántico genérico :math:`\\mathcal{E}` "
#~ "que actúa sobre una matriz de "
#~ "densidad :math:`\\rho` como:"

#~ msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = \\sum_i K_i \\rho K_i^\\dagger,"
#~ msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = \\sum_i K_i \\rho K_i^\\dagger,"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`K_i` are the Kraus "
#~ "operators satisfying the completeness relation"
#~ " :math:`\\sum_i K_i^\\dagger K_i = I`. "
#~ "The class is initialized with a "
#~ "list of Kraus operators given as "
#~ "QTensors."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "donde :math:`K_i` son los operadores de"
#~ " Kraus que satisfacen la relación de"
#~ " completitud :math:`\\sum_i K_i^\\dagger K_i "
#~ "= I`. La clase se inicializa con"
#~ " una lista de operadores de Kraus "
#~ "dados como QTensors."

#~ msgid "LindbladGenerator"
#~ msgstr "LindbladGenerator"

#~ msgid ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.LindbladGenerator` is "
#~ "a base class for analog noise "
#~ "models that use the Lindblad master "
#~ "equation to represent quantum noise "
#~ "processes. The Lindblad master equation "
#~ "describes the time evolution of a "
#~ "density matrix :math:`\\rho` under both "
#~ "unitary dynamics and dissipative processes:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.representations.LindbladGenerator` es "
#~ "una clase base para modelos de "
#~ "ruido analógico que usan la ecuación "
#~ "maestra de Lindblad para representar "
#~ "procesos de ruido cuántico. La ecuación"
#~ " maestra de Lindblad describe la "
#~ "evolución temporal de una matriz de "
#~ "densidad :math:`\\rho` bajo tanto la "
#~ "dinámica unitaria como los procesos "
#~ "disipativos:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\\frac{d\\rho}{dt} = -i[H, \\rho] + "
#~ "\\sum_i \\left( J_i \\rho J_i^\\dagger -"
#~ " \\frac{1}{2} \\{ J_i^\\dagger J_i, \\rho"
#~ " \\} \\right),"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "\\frac{d\\rho}{dt} = -i[H, \\rho] + "
#~ "\\sum_i \\left( J_i \\rho J_i^\\dagger -"
#~ " \\frac{1}{2} \\{ J_i^\\dagger J_i, \\rho"
#~ " \\} \\right),"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`H` is the system "
#~ "Hamiltonian, and :math:`J_i` are the "
#~ "jump operators representing different "
#~ "dissipation channels. The class is "
#~ "initialized with a list of jump "
#~ "operators given as QTensors and their"
#~ " corresponding rates (assumed to be 1"
#~ " if not specified)."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "donde :math:`H` es el Hamiltoniano del"
#~ " sistema, y :math:`J_i` son los "
#~ "operadores de salto que representan "
#~ "diferentes canales de disipación. La "
#~ "clase se inicializa con una lista "
#~ "de operadores de salto dados como "
#~ "QTensors y sus tasas correspondientes "
#~ "(se asume 1 si no se especifica)."

#~ msgid "PauliChannel"
#~ msgstr "PauliChannel"

#~ msgid ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` is a"
#~ " base class for noise models that "
#~ "use Pauli operators. A Pauli channel "
#~ "applies the Pauli operators (I, X, "
#~ "Y, Z) with certain probabilities. The"
#~ " channel can be represented as:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` es una"
#~ " clase base para modelos de ruido "
#~ "que usan operadores de Pauli. Un "
#~ "canal de Pauli aplica los operadores "
#~ "de Pauli (I, X, Y, Z) con "
#~ "ciertas probabilidades. El canal se "
#~ "puede representar como:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = p_I \\rho + p_X"
#~ " X \\rho X + p_Y Y \\rho "
#~ "Y + p_Z Z \\rho Z,"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = p_I \\rho + p_X"
#~ " X \\rho X + p_Y Y \\rho "
#~ "Y + p_Z Z \\rho Z,"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`p_I`, :math:`p_X`, :math:`p_Y`, "
#~ "and :math:`p_Z` are the probabilities "
#~ "for applying the respective Pauli "
#~ "operators, satisfying :math:`p_I + p_X +"
#~ " p_Y + p_Z = 1`. This "
#~ "corresponds to Kraus operators:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "donde :math:`p_I`, :math:`p_X`, :math:`p_Y` y"
#~ " :math:`p_Z` son las probabilidades de "
#~ "aplicar los respectivos operadores de "
#~ "Pauli, satisfaciendo :math:`p_I + p_X +"
#~ " p_Y + p_Z = 1`. Esto "
#~ "corresponde a los operadores de Kraus:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "K_0 = \\sqrt{p_I} I, \\quad K_1 ="
#~ " \\sqrt{p_X} X, \\quad K_2 = "
#~ "\\sqrt{p_Y} Y, \\quad K_3 = \\sqrt{p_Z}"
#~ " Z,"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "K_0 = \\sqrt{p_I} I, \\quad K_1 ="
#~ " \\sqrt{p_X} X, \\quad K_2 = "
#~ "\\sqrt{p_Y} Y, \\quad K_3 = \\sqrt{p_Z}"
#~ " Z,"

#~ msgid "Or jump operators:"
#~ msgstr "O como operadores de salto:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "J_1 = \\sqrt{\\gamma_X} X, \\quad J_2"
#~ " = \\sqrt{\\gamma_Y} Y, \\quad J_3 ="
#~ " \\sqrt{\\gamma_Z} Z,"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "J_1 = \\sqrt{\\gamma_X} X, \\quad J_2"
#~ " = \\sqrt{\\gamma_Y} Y, \\quad J_3 ="
#~ " \\sqrt{\\gamma_Z} Z,"

#~ msgid "where :math:`\\gamma_i` are rates related to the probabilities."
#~ msgstr "donde :math:`\\gamma_i` son tasas relacionadas con las probabilidades."

#~ msgid "BitFlip"
#~ msgstr "BitFlip"

#~ msgid ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.bit_flip.BitFlip` represents a "
#~ "bit-flip error model where each "
#~ "qubit has a certain probability of "
#~ "flipping its state from :math:`|0⟩` to"
#~ " :math:`|1⟩` or from :math:`|1⟩` to "
#~ ":math:`|0⟩`. This corresponds to the "
#~ "following channel:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.bit_flip.BitFlip` representa un "
#~ "modelo de error de inversión de "
#~ "bit donde cada qubit tiene cierta "
#~ "probabilidad de invertir su estado de"
#~ " :math:`|0⟩` a :math:`|1⟩` o de "
#~ ":math:`|1⟩` a :math:`|0⟩`. Esto corresponde"
#~ " al siguiente canal:"

#~ msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p X \\rho X,"
#~ msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p X \\rho X,"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`p` is the bit-flip "
#~ "probability. As such, it is a "
#~ "special case of "
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` with "
#~ ":math:`p_X = p` and :math:`p_I = 1"
#~ " - p`. This can therefore be "
#~ "written as Kraus operators:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "donde :math:`p` es la probabilidad de"
#~ " inversión de bit. Como tal, es "
#~ "un caso especial de "
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` con "
#~ ":math:`p_X = p` y :math:`p_I = 1"
#~ " - p`. Por lo tanto, se puede"
#~ " escribir como operadores de Kraus:"

#~ msgid "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} X,"
#~ msgstr "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} X,"

#~ msgid "or similarly as a jump operator:"
#~ msgstr "o de manera similar como operador de salto:"

#~ msgid "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} X,"
#~ msgstr "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} X,"

#~ msgid "where now :math:`\\gamma` is the bit-flip rate."
#~ msgstr "donde ahora :math:`\\gamma` es la tasa de inversión de bit."

#~ msgid "PhaseFlip"
#~ msgstr "PhaseFlip"

#~ msgid ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.phase_flip.PhaseFlip` represents a"
#~ " phase-flip error model where each"
#~ " qubit has a certain probability of"
#~ " flipping its phase, changing the "
#~ "sign of the :math:`|1⟩` state. This "
#~ "corresponds to the following channel:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.phase_flip.PhaseFlip` representa un"
#~ " modelo de error de inversión de "
#~ "fase donde cada qubit tiene cierta "
#~ "probabilidad de invertir su fase, "
#~ "cambiando el signo del estado "
#~ ":math:`|1⟩`. Esto corresponde al siguiente "
#~ "canal:"

#~ msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p Z \\rho Z,"
#~ msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho + p Z \\rho Z,"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`p` is the phase-flip "
#~ "probability. As such, it is a "
#~ "special case of "
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` with "
#~ ":math:`p_Z = p` and :math:`p_I = 1"
#~ " - p`. This can therefore be "
#~ "written as Kraus operators:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "donde :math:`p` es la probabilidad de"
#~ " inversión de fase. Como tal, es "
#~ "un caso especial de "
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` con "
#~ ":math:`p_Z = p` y :math:`p_I = 1"
#~ " - p`. Por lo tanto, se puede"
#~ " escribir como operadores de Kraus:"

#~ msgid "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} Z,"
#~ msgstr "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad K_1 = \\sqrt{p} Z,"

#~ msgid "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} Z,"
#~ msgstr "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} Z,"

#~ msgid "where now :math:`\\gamma` is the phase-flip rate."
#~ msgstr "donde ahora :math:`\\gamma` es la tasa de inversión de fase."

#~ msgid "Depolarizing"
#~ msgstr "Depolarizing"

#~ msgid ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.depolarizing.Depolarizing` represents "
#~ "a depolarizing error model where each"
#~ " qubit has a certain probability of"
#~ " being replaced by the maximally "
#~ "mixed state. This corresponds to the "
#~ "following channel:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.depolarizing.Depolarizing` representa "
#~ "un modelo de error despolarizador donde"
#~ " cada qubit tiene cierta probabilidad "
#~ "de ser reemplazado por el estado "
#~ "máximamente mezclado. Esto corresponde al "
#~ "siguiente canal:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho "
#~ "+ \\frac{p}{3} (X \\rho X + Y "
#~ "\\rho Y + Z \\rho Z),"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = (1 - p) \\rho "
#~ "+ \\frac{p}{3} (X \\rho X + Y "
#~ "\\rho Y + Z \\rho Z),"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`p` is the depolarizing "
#~ "probability. As such, it is a "
#~ "special case of "
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` with "
#~ ":math:`p_X = p_Y = p_Z = p/3` "
#~ "and :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. This "
#~ "can therefore be written as Kraus "
#~ "operators:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "donde :math:`p` es la probabilidad de"
#~ " despolarización. Como tal, es un "
#~ "caso especial de "
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.pauli_channel.PauliChannel` con "
#~ ":math:`p_X = p_Y = p_Z = p/3` "
#~ "y :math:`p_I = 1 - p`. Por "
#~ "lo tanto, se puede escribir como "
#~ "operadores de Kraus:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad "
#~ "K_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} X, \\quad K_2"
#~ " = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Y, \\quad K_3 "
#~ "= \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Z,"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "K_0 = \\sqrt{1 - p} I, \\quad "
#~ "K_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} X, \\quad K_2"
#~ " = \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Y, \\quad K_3 "
#~ "= \\sqrt{\\frac{p}{3}} Z,"

#~ msgid "or similarly as jump operators:"
#~ msgstr "o de manera similar como operadores de salto:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "J_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} X, \\quad "
#~ "J_2 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Y, \\quad "
#~ "J_3 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Z,"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "J_1 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} X, \\quad "
#~ "J_2 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Y, \\quad "
#~ "J_3 = \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma}{3}} Z,"

#~ msgid "where :math:`\\gamma` is the depolarizing rate."
#~ msgstr "donde :math:`\\gamma` es la tasa de despolarización."

#~ msgid "AmplitudeDamping"
#~ msgstr "AmplitudeDamping"

#~ msgid ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.amplitude_damping.AmplitudeDamping` "
#~ "represents an amplitude damping error "
#~ "model where each qubit has a "
#~ "certain probability of decaying from the"
#~ " excited state :math:`|1⟩` to the "
#~ "ground state :math:`|0⟩`. This corresponds "
#~ "to the following channel:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ ":class:`~qilisdk.noise.amplitude_damping.AmplitudeDamping` "
#~ "representa un modelo de error de "
#~ "amortiguamiento de amplitud donde cada "
#~ "qubit tiene cierta probabilidad de "
#~ "decaer desde el estado excitado "
#~ ":math:`|1⟩` al estado fundamental :math:`|0⟩`."
#~ " Esto corresponde al siguiente canal:"

#~ msgid "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = E_0 \\rho E_0^\\dagger + E_1 \\rho E_1^\\dagger."
#~ msgstr "\\mathcal{E}(\\rho) = E_0 \\rho E_0^\\dagger + E_1 \\rho E_1^\\dagger."

#~ msgid "Here the Kraus operators are defined as:"
#~ msgstr "Aquí los operadores de Kraus se definen como:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "E_0 = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\\\"
#~ " 0 & \\sqrt{1 - p} \\end{pmatrix},"
#~ " \\quad E_1 = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 &"
#~ " \\sqrt{p} \\\\ 0 & 0 \\end{pmatrix},"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "E_0 = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\\\"
#~ " 0 & \\sqrt{1 - p} \\end{pmatrix},"
#~ " \\quad E_1 = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 &"
#~ " \\sqrt{p} \\\\ 0 & 0 \\end{pmatrix},"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`p` is the amplitude damping"
#~ " probability. The channel can also be"
#~ " represented using the jump operator:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "donde :math:`p` es la probabilidad de"
#~ " amortiguamiento de amplitud. El canal "
#~ "también se puede representar usando el"
#~ " operador de salto:"

#~ msgid "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} \\sigma_-,"
#~ msgstr "J = \\sqrt{\\gamma} \\sigma_-,"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "where :math:`\\gamma` is the amplitude "
#~ "damping rate and :math:`\\sigma_-` is "
#~ "the lowering operator. The channel is"
